The paper discusses distributed consistency and coordination protocols, which are key topics in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also presents a program analysis framework that synthesizes coordination code, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of case studies in Twitter Storm and Bloom also suggests a focus on systems (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) may also be relevant.
